text: # Use this if you just want to keep it in a dataframe     df2 = pd.json_normalize(data['data']         df2['Timestamp'] = pd.Timestamp('now')  # Instead of to_datetime()     df_append = pd.DataFrame(df2)  # instead of df.append(df2)     df = pd.concat([df,df_append])  This is the code that worked for me.

author: @krystlestevens2585
text: TIP: around 12:17 when you run the API runner for the first time, I had to replace "df = df2.append(df2)" with     df_append = pd.DataFrame(df2)     df = pd.concat([df2,df_append])  because frame.append is deprecated; new format is panda.concat. I kept getting an annoying little warning message that I didn't want to show every time the runner was successful.  I typed this out on my own after a little research and I have to give a HUGE shoutout to Alex for the videos. I am FAR from versed in Python.... Just a little research and trial and error. Hope this helps someone!
